00:25:11,348 --> 00:25:12,521
Hold on.

281
00:25:12,807 --> 00:25:14,174
Get your hands off of me!

282
00:25:17,464 --> 00:25:19,270
Don't pretend you're cool

283
00:25:55,031 --> 00:25:58,031
We are working hard every day

284
00:25:58,130 --> 00:26:01,130
Minoru is a trainee

285
00:26:11,110 --> 00:26:15,331
Tsugio is skilled with his hands
and is learning about tabletops

286
00:26:17,873 --> 00:26:20,261
I am being taught electric welding

287
00:26:21,220 --> 00:26:24,220
I heard that this senior is someone who hasn't even graduate junior high school.

288
00:26:26,380 --> 00:26:30,027
I wear a mask to protect my eyes
from the welding

289
00:26:31,320 --> 00:26:40,177
Please rest assured that we will work hard to become skilled craftsmen. Best regards, Gonzō Yoshioka

290
00:26:41,352 --> 00:26:44,352
This is a letter from Yoshioka who went to the ironworks

291
00:26:45,020 --> 00:26:48,680
Next is a letter from Shiro and Makoto who went to the glass factory.

292
00:26:49,303 --> 00:26:50,103
I'll read them.

293
00:26:53,960 --> 00:26:56,400
Both of them are working hard and doing well.

294
00:26:57,180 --> 00:27:01,194
There are many glass factories in Tokyo, similar to the one we are working at

295
00:27:02,760 --> 00:27:05,086
The inside of the factory is really hot,

296
00:27:05,110 --> 00:27:06,346
but as you get used to the work,

297
00:27:06,370 --> 00:27:08,616
I start to find it interesting

298
00:27:08,640 --> 00:27:10,850
I want to get out quickly.

299
00:27:11,046 --> 00:27:16,227
I see, next is Watanabe who went to a soba shop.

300
00:27:20,878 --> 00:27:23,235
our lunch is at 3 o'clock

301
00:27:23,260 --> 00:27:25,846
I sometimes eat what customers leave behind

302
00:27:25,871 --> 00:27:30,267
So we eat anything, whether it's tempura rice bowl, oyakodon, or tamagodon

303
00:27:30,590 --> 00:27:31,940
It's really delicious

304
00:27:33,450 --> 00:27:37,623
But sometimes I get fed up with just going to the eat same foods, morning, noon, and night

305
00:27:38,642 --> 00:27:40,729
Hey ready?

306
00:27:44,071 --> 00:27:46,244
It's tough to deliver food.

307
00:27:46,370 --> 00:27:51,228
My senior, Macchan, can carry about 20 dishes.

308
00:27:51,905 --> 00:27:54,495
Of course, it took more than three years to get to learn this.

309
00:28:00,945 --> 00:28:02,271
Hey ready?

310
00:28:07,109 --> 00:28:08,649
Take care.

311
00:28:11,917 --> 00:28:12,763
Hey.

312
00:28:12,788 --> 00:28:14,870
Watch out.

313
00:28:15,715 --> 00:28:16,682
It was close.

314
00:28:18,722 --> 00:28:20,109
hey, this isn't a laughing matter

315
00:28:20,830 --> 00:28:21,530
Sorry.

316
00:28:23,020 --> 00:28:24,260
Hurry up.

317
00:28:26,463 --> 00:28:27,537
Take care.

318
00:28:36,645 --> 00:28:37,565
Ouch

319
00:28:44,012 --> 00:28:45,672
hey, this isn't a laughing matter

320
00:28:49,783 --> 00:28:52,783
Yeah, I'm sure I'll become a great soba shop owner

321
00:28:52,970 --> 00:28:58,164
Please say hello to everyone, and also to Teacher Ichiko Numata...

322
00:28:58,780 --> 00:29:01,807
You and Ichiko.....well, the rest doesn't really matter...

323
00:29:02,496 --> 00:29:07,054
Um, Tsuyoshi Nishiyama, who went to the auto repair shop.

324
00:29:09,753 --> 00:29:11,580
how is everyone doing?

325
00:29:12,900 --> 00:29:15,900
I have gotten used to both my work and the environment

326
00:29:17,870 --> 00:29:22,547
The mechanic has to learn how to drive the Ohto three-wheeler first

327
00:29:23,999 --> 00:29:25,717
Turn right.

328
00:29:28,661 --> 00:29:31,661
keep cutting

329
00:29:38,191 --> 00:29:38,924
More.

330
00:29:46,227 --> 00:29:47,293
Stop.

331
00:29:49,259 --> 00:29:50,799
Try going backwards.

332
00:29:55,443 --> 00:29:57,110
Hey.

333
00:29:59,170 --> 00:30:00,496
Try going backwards.

334
00:30:06,846 --> 00:30:07,798
Stop.

335
00:30:10,764 --> 00:30:12,190
What's wrong?

336
00:30:13,985 --> 00:30:15,573
I'm sorry

337
00:30:17,663 --> 00:30:18,583
Hey, you idiot!

338
00:30:19,270 --> 00:30:20,430
I'm sorry

339
00:30:27,099 --> 00:30:28,265
Inoue-sensei?

340
00:30:31,342 --> 00:30:32,645
Did you talk to that kid?

341
00:30:34,190 --> 00:30:35,629
Oh, I'll try talking to him today

342
00:30:47,290 --> 00:30:50,290
Inoue-kun,come

343
00:30:55,301 --> 00:30:55,915
What's wrong?

344
00:30:56,101 --> 00:30:57,001
Have a seat.

345
00:30:58,160 --> 00:31:00,287
this snack is really good, you know

346
00:31:03,200 --> 00:31:10,120
Actually, we need to start preparing for
next year's employment system, you know?

347
00:31:11,410 --> 00:31:14,086
Am I going to be the one doing it again?

348
00:31:14,111 --> 00:31:16,488
I was thinking of asking you for help

349
00:31:17,190 --> 00:31:18,867
You've gotten used to it.

350
00:31:19,639 --> 00:31:21,836
but if you say I'm used
to it, I can't deny that.

351
00:31:23,135 --> 00:31:24,597
I really don't want to get used to something like this

352
00:31:24,704 --> 00:31:26,157
Don't say like that.

353
00:31:27,148 --> 00:31:33,685
I think it's important for graduating students to find employment here

354
00:31:33,710 --> 00:31:34,554
I understand that

355
00:31:34,820 --> 00:31:37,820
Few students graduate from high school and go to college.

356
00:31:38,270 --> 00:31:42,783
But how many students can't do that.

357
00:31:43,780 --> 00:31:46,101
They will be the ones who lay the groundwork for society in the future

358
00:31:46,690 --> 00:31:50,215
In reality, they are the ones who will stand and support the foundation of the world

359
00:31:50,829 --> 00:31:53,829
I think they are the most important person

360
00:31:54,020 --> 00:31:57,853
Principal, I became a teacher

361
00:31:58,040 --> 00:31:59,039
because I want to be an educator

362
00:31:59,833 --> 00:32:02,479
I want to study more about myself while I still can

363
00:32:02,503 --> 00:32:03,495
I need some time

364
00:32:05,430 --> 00:32:08,010
Well, I can understand that

365
00:32:09,820 --> 00:32:12,820
You were a farmer's son, weren't you?

366
00:32:13,500 --> 00:32:16,146
Yes but so what?

367
00:32:17,159 --> 00:32:20,729
Living in the countryside is a big challenge.

368
00:32:21,540 --> 00:32:24,885
In any case, In the future, they will definitely have to go abroad to work.

369
00:32:26,749 --> 00:32:30,831
I won't force you to do this, but please think about it carefully.

370
00:32:32,237 --> 00:32:37,128
It's convenient for me that you, who understand the situation, will continue

371
00:32:55,702 --> 00:32:58,702
So, you didn't say a word about marriage?

372
00:33:00,202 --> 00:33:01,893
It's okay if I talk to the principal!

373
00:33:01,918 --> 00:33:02,862
Don't worry.

374
00:33:03,788 --> 00:33:05,167
I'm not going to take the principal's daughter

375
00:33:06,560 --> 00:33:07,885
I'm going to take you

376
00:33:08,430 --> 00:33:11,636
We should just submit a marriage
notification to the principal

377
00:33:11,660 --> 00:33:13,362
and say that if he wants to come to the wedding

378
00:33:24,830 --> 00:33:25,940
What's wrong?

379
00:33:27,080 --> 00:33:29,510
It seems like they can't take a break because of the work

380
00:33:29,830 --> 00:33:31,495
But today is the third day.

381
00:33:31,972 --> 00:33:34,823
Tsugio is currently negotiating., but I wonder if it will go well

382
00:33:37,005 --> 00:33:39,510
I've got urgent work piling up today

383
00:33:39,991 --> 00:33:41,463
I've decided to cancel my day off

384
00:33:42,090 --> 00:33:45,090
Our situation is different from your thriving factory

385
00:34:18,615 --> 00:34:21,615
Hey, what are you looking at?

386
00:34:21,640 --> 00:34:24,640
You didn't come to Tokyo just to have fun.
You're here to work

387
00:34:35,132 --> 00:34:36,917
Excuse me, President

388
00:34:37,612 --> 00:34:38,659
What?

389
00:34:40,862 --> 00:34:43,042
 I would like to go to night school

390
00:34:43,489 --> 00:34:44,195
night school?

391
00:34:44,220 --> 00:34:45,979
That was the promise we made at the start.

392
00:34:47,200 --> 00:34:48,936
Workers don't need education

393
00:34:48,961 --> 00:34:50,996
It's just a waste of time

394
00:34:51,970 --> 00:34:55,510
You should say that when you can do the job properly.

395
00:34:57,990 --> 00:34:59,409
What should we do?

396
00:34:59,714 --> 00:35:00,831
Lets go home

397
00:35:02,690 --> 00:35:05,175
what should we send as a wedding gift for the teacher?

398
00:35:05,200 --> 00:35:06,926
Look for it in the department store

399
00:35:06,950 --> 00:35:09,635
Let's also cover Shiro and Makoto's share.

400
00:35:11,159 --> 00:35:12,575
let's go to Asakusa today

401
00:35:12,600 --> 00:35:14,870
It's boring, I went there the other day

402
00:35:15,150 --> 00:35:16,556
Hey, how about going somewhere to take a boat.

403
00:35:16,580 --> 00:35:18,616
Sounds good, I'm in!

404
00:35:18,641 --> 00:35:21,641
I thought that Mr. Inoue and Ms. Ichiko had a dating

405
00:35:22,540 --> 00:35:24,276
Don't say bullshit.

406
00:35:24,690 --> 00:35:26,436
Let's buy some gifts soon

407
00:35:26,460 --> 00:35:27,996
Which department shall we go to?

408
00:35:28,020 --> 00:35:31,020
There are as many department stores in Tokyo as there are tobacco shops.

409
00:36:18,214 --> 00:36:19,401
They are here

410
00:36:20,055 --> 00:36:21,424
it looks like a lovely bride

411
00:36:24,985 --> 00:36:27,985
Don't push me.

412
00:36:48,456 --> 00:36:50,631
Oh.

413
00:36:50,806 --> 00:36:52,702
Where have you been?

414
00:36:53,538 --> 00:36:54,932
I went to buy this

415
00:36:55,386 --> 00:36:57,323
You don't have to be drunk.

416
00:36:57,767 --> 00:36:59,994
Now it's time to show off our skills

417
00:37:03,444 --> 00:37:05,448
We just finished

418
00:37:05,473 --> 00:37:07,534
It was tough.

419
00:37:09,597 --> 00:37:10,776
 please

420
00:37:12,540 --> 00:37:15,276
Wow, this is The principal's wife

421
00:37:15,323 --> 00:37:16,752
Thank you very much for everything.

422
00:37:16,777 --> 00:37:18,776
Everything ended safely.

423
00:37:18,801 --> 00:37:20,277
Congratulations!

424
00:37:20,401 --> 00:37:21,769
Come here

425
00:37:22,501 --> 00:37:25,501
Well then, I'll be waiting for you later

426
00:37:31,807 --> 00:37:33,115
What do you want to do?

427
00:37:33,140 --> 00:37:35,716
Everyone has been looking for you,

428
00:37:40,178 --> 00:37:43,178
I bought a new one.

429
00:37:47,827 --> 00:37:50,502
There are many customers who don't drink alcohol.

430
00:37:51,240 --> 00:37:53,576
Look, that person hates alcohol

431
00:37:53,600 --> 00:37:56,600
Unfortunately

432
00:37:56,909 --> 00:37:59,144
Call Ishiya.

433
00:38:00,230 --> 00:38:02,464
Come.

434
00:38:13,581 --> 00:38:15,850
Osono

435
00:38:15,900 --> 00:38:17,737
It seems that Ichiro has returned,

436
00:38:17,762 --> 00:38:18,659
but what's going on?

437
00:38:19,050 --> 00:38:22,050
He seems to have some urgent business.

438
00:38:22,180 --> 00:38:25,995
He doesn't go to a job

439
00:38:36,935 --> 00:38:39,151
It's all over.

440
00:38:42,650 --> 00:38:44,876
Well, it seems like everything is just about done

441
00:38:44,900 --> 00:38:45,729
Yeah.

442
00:38:46,151 --> 00:38:47,183
Where is my sewing machine?

443
00:38:47,208 --> 00:38:49,745
I placed an order so I'll deliver it when it arrives.

444
00:38:51,050 --> 00:38:52,417
That was very expensive.

445
00:38:52,794 --> 00:38:55,104
Hey, I only got a sewing machine from my brother

446
00:38:56,030 --> 00:38:57,316
Thank you very much

447
00:38:57,340 --> 00:38:58,726
Thank you for your hard work

448
00:38:58,750 --> 00:39:00,666
Well, let's have dinner then

449
00:39:00,690 --> 00:39:02,049
Okay, I'll go this way

450
00:39:04,900 --> 00:39:09,016
I used all my savings for everything else,
even bought Shelf stuff.

451
00:39:09,040 --> 00:39:11,690
It's too late for you to complain to me
now; until now.

452
00:39:11,848 --> 00:39:16,600
I was putting all my salary into everyone
else's needs without even buying what I wanted

453
00:39:16,710 --> 00:39:18,266
You have no right to complain to me

454
00:39:18,290 --> 00:39:22,049
What? Then I'll say it to you.

455
00:39:22,848 --> 00:39:24,736
Who do you think
helped me earn until today?

456
00:39:25,440 --> 00:39:27,167
Thanks to whom was I able to go to school?

457
00:39:27,840 --> 00:39:30,840
It's been six years since our dad fell ill, and it's like a different world

458
00:39:30,979 --> 00:39:34,002
If I keep sending tuition every month,
who would forget?

459
00:39:34,938 --> 00:39:37,938
Brother, you don't like that I didn't go to Yamazaki's place, do you?

460
00:39:39,800 --> 00:39:42,800
I don't like Inoue.

461
00:39:43,823 --> 00:39:45,269
What's the hell?

462
00:39:45,705 --> 00:39:46,799
He is a really bad guy

463
00:39:47,520 --> 00:39:50,463
So I even held
the wedding at my house, didn't I?

464
00:39:52,379 --> 00:39:53,565
Now, let's go to the tatami room

465
00:39:53,590 --> 00:39:54,463
Come on, brother

466
00:39:55,033 --> 00:39:57,018
You will probably regret it later

467
00:39:57,045 --> 00:39:58,768
you really say some awful things

468
00:40:00,070 --> 00:40:01,546
If I marry to that agricultural cooperative person,

469
00:40:01,570 --> 00:40:03,292
Sure, it might be convenient for you,

470
00:40:03,942 --> 00:40:06,668
but I won't always go along with your convenience

471
00:40:06,997 --> 00:40:08,853
You did try to use me.

472
00:40:09,920 --> 00:40:11,299
I understand it properly, you know

473
00:40:11,671 --> 00:40:14,893
You're making a face like you oppose this marriage, aren't you?

474
00:40:14,918 --> 00:40:18,104
What? Don't say like that.

475
00:40:18,270 --> 00:40:19,406
That's true.

476
00:40:19,430 --> 00:40:19,916
Come here

477
00:40:19,940 --> 00:40:20,736
What are you talking about!

478
00:40:22,047 --> 00:40:23,849
Stop it.

479
00:40:25,090 --> 00:40:28,307
Today is her celebration day.

480
00:40:28,970 --> 00:40:30,432
Damn it.

481
00:40:35,069 --> 00:40:37,235
Everything is over.

482
00:40:37,260 --> 00:40:38,893
please take this

483
00:40:41,012 --> 00:40:43,108
Hey you too.

484
00:40:43,596 --> 00:40:46,877
My legs hurt so I want to stretch them

485
00:40:47,517 --> 00:40:49,619
Let's take it easy.

486
00:40:50,806 --> 00:40:52,757
Where is the bride?

487
00:40:52,880 --> 00:40:53,752
Ah, I see, I see

488
00:40:56,964 --> 00:40:59,073
She's coming.

489
00:41:03,104 --> 00:41:05,235
Sorry for keeping you waiting.

490
00:41:07,590 --> 00:41:10,590
what's going on here?

491
00:41:16,089 --> 00:41:16,964
What's wrong?

492
00:41:18,190 --> 00:41:21,058
Inoue-san, let's have a drink together.

493
00:41:23,253 --> 00:41:28,706
A man should get married and have a family

494
00:41:29,526 --> 00:41:32,245
After that it gradually calms down

495
00:41:32,433 --> 00:41:35,167
I don't want to do any more job placements.

496
00:41:36,183 --> 00:41:38,214
Don't say bullshit.

497
00:41:39,872 --> 00:41:43,291
Someone from the school is here

498
00:41:44,974 --> 00:41:47,974
I wonder if something's wrong?

499
00:41:52,511 --> 00:41:53,401
What's wrong?

500
00:41:53,578 --> 00:41:56,578
A telegram arrived from Tokyo.

501
00:41:59,300 --> 00:42:02,643
There seems to have been some problem with the student who got the job.

502
00:42:03,740 --> 00:42:04,909
Thank you for your work.

503
00:42:06,511 --> 00:42:07,315
What's wrong?

504
00:42:07,565 --> 00:42:09,409
A telegram arrived from Tokyo.

505
00:42:11,750 --> 00:42:14,750
Two people from the glass factory have dropped out

506
00:42:15,541 --> 00:42:18,541
Please contact us immediately.

507
00:42:19,472 --> 00:42:22,120
They must be Shiro and Makoto.

508
00:42:22,560 --> 00:42:24,518
They come back here?

509
00:42:24,635 --> 00:42:26,649
I think they will contact you if they are back.

510
00:42:27,189 --> 00:42:28,705
I will go to Tokyo

511
00:42:29,190 --> 00:42:30,806
Are you really going?

512
00:42:30,830 --> 00:42:35,127
your bride must be feeling sad, right?

513
00:42:35,495 --> 00:42:37,675
Don't worry.
Let's go

514
00:42:37,980 --> 00:42:39,106
I want to go too.

515
00:42:39,130 --> 00:42:41,312
That's better. It's good
to go together, isn't it?

516
00:42:42,181 --> 00:42:43,760
Sorry about that

517
00:42:44,087 --> 00:42:45,815
You should prepare

518
00:42:45,840 --> 00:42:48,034
Thank you everyone.

519
00:42:49,139 --> 00:42:51,436
You have had a tough time.

520
00:42:54,407 --> 00:42:57,407
It's my responsibility when it comes to those kids

521
00:43:14,560 --> 00:43:17,560
I'm really sorry to you

522
00:43:22,280 --> 00:43:24,260
Just think of it as a honeymoon trip

523
00:43:27,042 --> 00:43:30,042
A honeymoon trip, huh,

524
00:43:34,900 --> 00:43:37,336
I received a call from the Ueno police station late

525
00:43:38,040 --> 00:43:41,784
They were apparently taken into custody as part of a crackdown on delinquent youth.

526
00:43:42,330 --> 00:43:44,716
I went ahead and contacted the glass factory just in case

527
00:43:44,740 --> 00:43:46,016
The police are over there

528
00:43:50,140 --> 00:43:50,901
teacher?

529
00:43:53,595 --> 00:43:55,987
What happened to you guys?

530
00:43:56,214 --> 00:43:57,980
They said you left the factory two days ago

531
00:43:58,560 --> 00:44:01,560
We were looking for another job

532
00:44:02,050 --> 00:44:06,557
We were in a pachinko parlor.

533
00:44:09,252 --> 00:44:10,206
So, you guys

534
00:44:10,230 --> 00:44:12,446
Did you leave because you hated that factory?

535
00:44:12,470 --> 00:44:14,776
If you didn't like it, you should have told Muto.

536
00:44:15,260 --> 00:44:17,385
I thought it was useless to do that

537
00:44:19,214 --> 00:44:20,534
sit down.

538
00:44:21,939 --> 00:44:24,965
There were many things that were different from the initial promise.

539
00:44:24,990 --> 00:44:26,752
What do you mean?

540
00:44:28,700 --> 00:44:31,432
There are many people in the world without jobs,

541
00:44:31,838 --> 00:44:33,386
you can't say that in those situations

542
00:44:33,588 --> 00:44:35,886
Teacher, we don't have holiday either

543
00:44:35,910 --> 00:44:38,910
When they said they would give me a salary of 2500 yen, it turned out to be 1500 yen

544
00:44:39,030 --> 00:44:41,166
When they said they would let us go to night school, but it was a lie

545
00:44:41,190 --> 00:44:42,196
In between work, we take care of the dog,

546
00:44:42,220 --> 00:44:45,042
fill the bath with water, and work
every night

547
00:44:46,030 --> 00:44:48,186
I'm too tired to write the letter

548
00:44:48,217 --> 00:44:50,917
